1
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:06,960
Here.

2
00:00:08,119 --> 00:00:09,080
The last two dishes.

3
00:00:09,359 --> 00:00:10,439
Just home cooking.

4
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:11,519
Grab a bite.

5
00:00:12,359 --> 00:00:13,960
Thanks for the hard work, brother-in-law.

6
00:00:14,119 --> 00:00:15,279
You've all worked hard.

7
00:00:15,279 --> 00:00:16,440
Busy all day, huh?

8
00:00:16,839 --> 00:00:17,679
Just running around.

9
00:00:18,359 --> 00:00:18,920
Come on.

10
00:00:19,160 --> 00:00:20,000
Alright, cheers.

11
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,359
Lately,

12
00:00:22,719 --> 00:00:24,359
Min Shengquan,

13
00:00:25,079 --> 00:00:25,960
Chen Yongjiang,

14
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,399
Zhang Yuanshan,

15
00:00:27,879 --> 00:00:30,239
they're all tangled up in this Feng Mao business.

16
00:00:30,679 --> 00:00:32,079
Calling you down to the station,

17
00:00:32,079 --> 00:00:33,320
it's just a formality.

18
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:34,439
Don't take it to heart.

19
00:00:36,439 --> 00:00:38,000
When the police are working a case,

20
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:39,799
we've got to cooperate.

21
00:00:40,039 --> 00:00:40,560
Right?

22
00:00:40,799 --> 00:00:41,679
Right, cooperate.

23
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:43,200
It's only right.

24
00:00:44,439 --> 00:00:45,039
Exactly.

25
00:00:46,359 --> 00:00:47,439
It's a society of laws.

26
00:00:47,799 --> 00:00:49,880
You need evidence to arrest someone, right?

27
00:00:50,039 --> 00:00:50,439
Right.

28
00:00:50,439 --> 00:00:51,159
Come on, cheers.

29
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:52,840
A toast to a society of laws.

30
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:53,479
To a society of laws.

31
00:00:53,479 --> 00:00:54,039
Come on, come on.

32
00:00:54,119 --> 00:00:54,799
Society of laws.

33
00:00:56,079 --> 00:00:56,679
Cheers.

34
00:01:08,519 --> 00:01:10,000
I remember when you first got out,

35
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,920
I set you up with a job

36
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,760
patrolling at that fishery.

37
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,120
How did you end up

38
00:01:17,159 --> 00:01:18,560
running with Chen Yongjiang?

39
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,400
Wanted to make money.

40
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,200
Make money.

41
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:28,840
Making money's nothing shameful.

42
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,120
Money's so hard to come by these days.

43
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,519
Forget about Datou,

44
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:35,439
even me,

45
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,799
once the kid was born,

46
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:40,079
felt like money was short everywhere.

47
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,239
Working with Feng Mao,

48
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,120
whether big jobs or small,

49
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:47,200
at least we could get by, right?

50
00:01:48,879 --> 00:01:49,719
I see.

51
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,760
So you mean now that Feng Mao's done,

52
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:55,480
you're rolling with our Bro Xiao now, right?

53
00:01:57,159 --> 00:01:59,159
Brother-in-law, don't shame me.

54
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,840
At first,

55
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,439
nobody at Feng Mao really dealt with me.

56
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:07,640
On Chen Yongjiang's side, I only knew Datou.

57
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,840
Later, after the law firm fired me,

58
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,360
I had to rely on the kid to throw me some work.

59
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,800
At the auto repair shop,

60
00:02:16,479 --> 00:02:18,120
don't go butting in.

61
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:20,800
Hey, Brother-in-law,

62
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,680
you didn't used to talk this much.

63
00:02:24,719 --> 00:02:27,199
I'm asking him, why are you jumping in?

64
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30,400
We rarely get a chance to drink together.

65
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:32,639
How can I not talk more?

66
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,479
Come on.

67
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,120
Here, try these bamboo shoots.

68
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:50,599
How's it going on Min Shengquan's side?

69
00:02:54,439 --> 00:02:56,120
No work talk at the dinner table.

70
00:02:56,599 --> 00:02:57,680
Just thinking about it is upsetting.

71
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,879
A Min's definitely not getting out, right?

72
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:01,439
What a question.

73
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:04,360
Dismemberment and mutilation, two lives.

74
00:03:04,479 --> 00:03:05,199
How could he get out?

75
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:09,759
How do you know about the dismemberment and mutilation?

76
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,159
It's all over the news.

77
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:23,360
The TV stations run it on repeat every day.

78
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,439
You know, that one...

79
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,800
The Old Dock thing.

80
00:03:25,919 --> 00:03:27,000
Right? The Old Dock.

81
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:27,919
It's been reported.

82
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,719
I was just scrolling through it the other day.

83
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:31,520
Reported.

84
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:32,759
And another thing...

85
00:03:34,039 --> 00:03:35,159
Our town's small.

86
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:37,039
You hear bits of it everywhere you go.

87
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:39,680
I even heard that inside the fish's belly,

88
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,120
they found human tissue.

89
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,400
Something like this in a small county...

90
00:03:43,479 --> 00:03:44,400
It's pretty terrifying.

91
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:47,159
A Min's got some nerve, doesn't he?

92
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:51,479
The police haven't even officially announced it.

93
00:03:51,479 --> 00:03:52,879
And the media already broke it.

94
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:56,479
What a mess, seriously.

95
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,199
Unbelievable.

96
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,000
You guys need to file a complaint.

97
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:00,800
Sure.

98
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,680
It's interfering with your police work.

99
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:03,919
Come on, drink up.

100
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,000
Cheers.

101
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:07,080
They can't just do whatever.

102
00:04:07,199 --> 00:04:08,240
They can't just do whatever.

103
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,199
No messing around, no messing around, no messing around.

104
00:04:15,719 --> 00:04:16,879
Let me tell you, Boss.

105
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:20,959
Liquor makes people tell the truth.

106
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:21,519
Right.

107
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:25,560
And liquor can make people walk a straight line.

108
00:04:27,079 --> 00:04:27,360
Right.

109
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,399
Having fun drinking with me?

110
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,399
A blast, Bro.

111
00:04:29,639 --> 00:04:31,759
Let's do it again next time.

112
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:32,439
Sure, sure, sure.

113
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Come on, let's go.

114
00:04:34,199 --> 00:04:35,800
Take him home. Take him home for me.

115
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,319
What are you doing?

116
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,519
Let the Boss take me back.

117
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,160
A designated driver...

118
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,480
What designated driver?

119
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,279
You there?

120
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,680
Don't even have my keys on me.

121
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,360
Anyone there?

122
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:46,680
No keys, no keys.

123
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,680
Brother-in-law, brother-in-law, calm down.

124
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,800
The rideshare you booked is almost here.

125
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,800
At my level, shouldn't we...

126
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,240
What level? What level are you?

127
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,360
You take good care of him.

128
00:04:57,439 --> 00:04:57,800
Got it, Bro.

129
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,959
See him off, hurry up.

130
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,480
He's a Captain, after all.

131
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,720
Hurry, let's go, Datou.

132
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,800
Hurry, hurry.

133
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,720
Drop me a message when you get home.

134
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:04,279
Will do.

135
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,240
Don't worry, Bro.

136
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:05,959
We're off.

137
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:14,600
Officer.

138
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,759
This is a completely clean establishment.

139
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:17,680
Let me see.

140
00:05:18,079 --> 00:05:18,759
Search the place.

141
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:19,959
ID card.

142
00:05:21,079 --> 00:05:22,680
Based on the leads from Economic Crime Investigation,

143
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,720
Lao Ma, you and Zhao Dian lead the team.

144
00:05:24,959 --> 00:05:26,600
On the surface, it's a routine safety check.

145
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,560
The longer it takes,

146
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:29,519
the better cover I'll have to gather evidence.

147
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,000
Line up.

148
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:50,879
Let me see your IDs.

149
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:56,160
Officer, we definitely don't have

150
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,839
any of those massage things you mentioned.

151
00:05:58,879 --> 00:05:59,639
What did you say?

152
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:25,319
Hello, welcome to Greenland Cemetery.

153
00:06:25,879 --> 00:06:28,120
We are a garden for kings,

154
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,160
a memorial for the living.

155
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:32,800
On this road,

156
00:06:33,879 --> 00:06:35,120
there's only one cemetery.

157
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,879
What would Luo Xiao go to a cemetery for?

158
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:53,279
Jin Qiang.

159
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,800
Take some men over there to check it out.

160
00:06:55,199 --> 00:06:55,839
Got it.

161
00:06:56,639 --> 00:06:57,600
We'll contact you if anything comes up.

162
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,480
Sure, sure, sure.

163
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,439
Come on, come here.

164
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:11,920
You're just on a paycheck, right?

165
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,480
No need to take the fall for someone else, right?

166
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,519
What if they're criminals?

167
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:15,680
Let's just be straight with each other.

168
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,000
Who else has been to this warehouse?

169
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,920
Chen Yongjiang was making a movie.

170
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:32,160
Really thinks he's some mob boss.

171
00:07:34,399 --> 00:07:35,439
The coffin's been tampered with.

172
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:40,240
Just him. He also said it's Feng Mao's.

173
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:41,399
Doesn't know anything else.

174
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:43,120
Call him.

175
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:51,720
Boss.

176
00:07:52,519 --> 00:07:55,519
A police chief came to the warehouse looking for something.

177
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,199
He wants to talk to you.

178
00:08:04,759 --> 00:08:05,399
Hang up.

179
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,399
This is bad.

180
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:14,079
What's wrong, Bro?

181
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,360
What's wrong, Bro?

182
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,560
What happened?

183
00:08:49,399 --> 00:08:51,360
Answer it. Tell the truth. Answer.

184
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:54,559
Hello?

185
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:55,720
Hello?

186
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,559
The signal was bad just now.

187
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,720
What's going on?

188
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:03,320
A police chief came to the warehouse looking for something.

189
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:05,200
Said he wants to talk to you.

190
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,399
Did you need something?

191
00:09:11,279 --> 00:09:12,000
Brother-in-law.

192
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:13,960
Zhang Heng.

193
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:17,039
It's really you. I thought it sounded like you.

194
00:09:18,919 --> 00:09:20,440
What are you investigating?

195
00:09:21,039 --> 00:09:22,879
How can I help?

196
00:09:23,639 --> 00:09:24,600
It's nothing.

197
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,080
Where are you right now?

198
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,440
I'm at the auto repair shop.

199
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:28,279
I'm working.

200
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,879
Alright, I'll come find you.

201
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:34,320
Okay.

202
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:39,720
Dian.

203
00:09:40,399 --> 00:09:41,000
Let's go.

204
00:09:56,919 --> 00:09:59,759
How the hell did Zhang Heng find the warehouse?

205
00:10:02,679 --> 00:10:03,240
Bro.

206
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,679
They'll be here soon.

207
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,519
Should I leave first?

208
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,600
Go.

209
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:13,200
Okay.

210
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,279
Right, right.

211
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,399
Come on, let's go.

212
00:10:33,039 --> 00:10:34,399
This place isn't bad.

213
00:10:40,159 --> 00:10:41,720
You guys fix these cars too?

214
00:10:43,039 --> 00:10:44,799
This one's huge.

215
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,759
Brother-in-law.

216
00:10:45,919 --> 00:10:46,960
You're here, brother-in-law.

217
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,039
Come, sit. Business looks good.

218
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:50,320
Such big trucks outside.

219
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:51,799
Didn't you leave?

220
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,759
Why are you back?

221
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,879
Ran into Captain Zhang on the way.

222
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,440
Saw him while waiting at a light.

223
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:58,360
Figured I'd come chat with you guys.

224
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,159
Sit, sit. Sit over here.

225
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,240
Datou, you come here every day?

226
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,039
Yeah.

227
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,919
He's a minor shareholder.

228
00:11:08,639 --> 00:11:10,399
Helped me raise some funds at the start.

229
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,440
Now he helps me with the books,

230
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:13,559
running errands and stuff.

231
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:18,000
So what brings you here?

232
00:11:19,159 --> 00:11:20,200
We received a tip-off

233
00:11:20,759 --> 00:11:23,080
that Yi Mao Foot Bath Center offered sex services.

234
00:11:23,519 --> 00:11:24,759
When we went to inspect,

235
00:11:24,799 --> 00:11:25,879
we found some photos.

236
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,279
All companies Chen Yongjiang has shares in.

237
00:11:28,399 --> 00:11:31,519
One of them was Greenland Cemetery.

238
00:11:32,639 --> 00:11:34,440
We're here today to find out

239
00:11:35,039 --> 00:11:36,039
in this Greenland Cemetery,

240
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,919
who the contact person for Chen Yongjiang's warehouse is.

241
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,200
Why is it you again?

242
00:11:41,879 --> 00:11:43,120
As for me,

243
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:45,200
I've been Mr. Chen's legal representative

244
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,279
for five years now.

245
00:11:48,759 --> 00:11:51,360
Many of his work and personal affairs

246
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,279
are entrusted to me.

247
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,320
Have you been to the warehouse?

248
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:57,639
Yes.

249
00:11:59,279 --> 00:12:00,200
It used to store

250
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,240
some of Mr. Chen's personal belongings.

251
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,639
After he went missing,

252
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,480
Ms. Huang Qiuping asked me

253
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:10,000
to go pick up a few things.

254
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:10,879
What did you pick up?

255
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,399
They were getting divorced, right?

256
00:12:19,159 --> 00:12:20,720
Ms. Huang asked me

257
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:23,080
to investigate all of Mr. Chen's assets.

258
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:26,840
So I went to retrieve some project contracts.

259
00:12:28,919 --> 00:12:30,879
Contracts kept in a warehouse?

260
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,639
And a cemetery warehouse at that?

261
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:42,240
This is just...

262
00:12:42,919 --> 00:12:43,960
It might be...

263
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,639
Maybe it's the boss's personal quirk.

264
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,320
I really can't say for sure.

265
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:49,879
Datou.

266
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:51,519
Top me up with some water.

267
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:52,679
Sure.

268
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:53,919
Thanks.

269
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:55,039
That kettle of mine...

270
00:12:56,279 --> 00:12:57,320
is a real pain to use.

271
00:12:57,559 --> 00:12:59,080
It whistles before it's even done.

272
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,559
Get yourself a better kettle later.

273
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:03,440
Next time the officer comes, he needs it hot.

274
00:13:04,159 --> 00:13:04,759
Got it.

275
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:05,720
A bit more.

276
00:13:07,399 --> 00:13:09,399
There was money in that coffin.

277
00:13:16,159 --> 00:13:16,919
Real money.

278
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,440
Actual cash.

279
00:13:24,559 --> 00:13:25,360
Did you put it there?

280
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:29,679
I'm not crazy.

281
00:13:29,759 --> 00:13:31,600
Why would I put money in there?

282
00:13:32,399 --> 00:13:34,559
Then why were you sneaking around that day?

283
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:39,799
Officer, I just remembered.

284
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:43,000
Before Huang Qiuping's burial,

285
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,200
